206
00:26:33,074 --> 00:26:41,862
That's the foundation of what it means to be proud of our city, of what allows us to strive for excellence, of how we work to restore faith in our city and in each other.

207
00:26:43,058 --> 00:26:51,287
We have great projects to accomplish for Medford over these next two years, especially our new Medford High School that we're about to hear about from member Graham.

208
00:26:52,668 --> 00:26:54,310
And we must come together to achieve them.

209
00:26:55,371 --> 00:27:00,156
I will bring my deepest well of compassion and dedication to seeing those accomplishments become reality.

210
00:27:00,817 --> 00:27:02,819
And I welcome every neighbor to walk that path together.

211
00:27:03,159 --> 00:27:03,440
Thank you.

212
00:27:13,118 --> 00:27:16,921
I'd like to welcome school committee member Jenny Graham to give an update on Medford High School.

213
00:27:30,711 --> 00:27:31,432
Hello everyone.

214
00:27:34,453 --> 00:27:39,617
for asking me to speak today, and for all the work that we've done together for the last six years.

215
00:27:39,637 --> 00:27:46,243
It feels like the longest and shortest six years of my life, as many of you know.

216
00:27:46,263 --> 00:27:54,249
I never really set out to be a politician, and I still don't think that quite fits what I would call myself, but I'll talk a little bit about the high school.

217
00:27:55,150 --> 00:28:02,253
In my first campaign, my palm card said, develop a comprehensive and holistic plan to address the future of each of our school buildings.

218
00:28:02,753 --> 00:28:06,374
See the first go around, you walk some fine lines because you want to be elected.

219
00:28:07,594 --> 00:28:09,235
I guess I am a politician after all.

220
00:28:11,216 --> 00:28:15,437
In that first year, I also said something like, work for increased and fair funding for our schools.

221
00:28:15,977 --> 00:28:17,258
Today, I'd be more direct.

222
00:28:17,898 --> 00:28:21,539
We need a new Medford High School, and our schools are underfunded and need more.

223
00:28:22,139 --> 00:28:23,620
So that's my six years ago.

224
00:28:30,575 --> 00:28:39,004
But what I've learned along the way is people appreciate that directness, and people appreciate people who will stand up and say, there's something wrong, and we have to fix it.

225
00:28:39,024 --> 00:28:43,889
Scott and I have lived here for 10 years, and we are new by some standards.

226
00:28:44,369 --> 00:28:48,493
And we have been welcomed by many people who have been here much, much longer than us.

227
00:28:49,495 --> 00:28:53,919
And when our kids were very young, we had to go to Medford High School, and it was stunning.

228
00:28:54,860 --> 00:28:56,381
Like I stepped back in time.

229
00:28:57,062 --> 00:29:02,547
So I feel like I stepped further back in time than even my high school, and I graduated in 1995.

230
00:29:03,688 --> 00:29:07,972
My high school felt more modern in my memory than what I was looking at in Medford High School.

231
00:29:09,313 --> 00:29:14,418
And it actually gave me pause to say, is this really the place for us for the long term?

232
00:29:16,272 --> 00:29:21,595
And then, you know, we put our kids in school and we got to know our neighbors and we're like, yes, this is the place for us.

233
00:29:22,276 --> 00:29:26,618
But wow, high school still looked like a relic.

234
00:29:27,239 --> 00:29:29,180
And I kept hoping that somebody

235
00:29:30,022 --> 00:29:32,665
would do something to fix it.

236
00:29:33,506 --> 00:29:34,567
So fast forward, here we are.

237
00:29:34,627 --> 00:29:37,289
Apparently, I'm one of the somebodies who would do something.

238
00:29:38,631 --> 00:29:42,435
And I'm super excited because we're finally getting to do something.

239
00:29:43,456 --> 00:29:48,541
For the record, the list of volunteers and the somebodies who are going to do something is in the hundreds at this point.

240
00:29:48,601 --> 00:29:51,784
It's becoming a very long spreadsheet that will get longer as we go.

241
00:29:53,165 --> 00:29:56,427
In 2022, we submitted a bid to the MSBA and we were finalists.

242
00:29:57,187 --> 00:30:04,170
But because of record inflation and the number of programs that were competing for a limited amount of money, we did not proceed, we did not go forward.

243
00:30:05,750 --> 00:30:07,711
In 2023, we did it again and we got in.

244
00:30:08,111 --> 00:30:11,052
So I was like, yes, as the kids say, let's go.

245
00:30:11,072 --> 00:30:16,835
But then we learned that this process is a process.

246
00:30:17,595 --> 00:30:21,039
And the MSBA takes its role as stewards of taxpayer dollars really seriously.

247
00:30:21,660 --> 00:30:30,971
So we've worked alongside them through the process, which is tedious at times, but we push, and I'm pushy, and we want to move fast because that's what our kids deserve.

248
00:30:32,564 --> 00:30:41,733
As the chair, we have found a bunch of equally pushy people willing to push through these initial phases just as fast as we can because this community values action.

249
00:30:42,634 --> 00:30:44,276
In this instance, though, paperwork comes first.

250
00:30:44,716 --> 00:30:48,620
So that's what we've been up to for the last two years and what feels like an eternity.

251
00:30:49,341 --> 00:30:53,345
I am thrilled, though, to say that we're on the paperwork phase really rapidly.

252
00:30:53,885 --> 00:30:56,388
We've hired a project management company and an architect.

253
00:30:56,968 --> 00:31:08,815
They're on board and they're working hard and fast to explore the site, to understand, to talk to our educators, hundreds of them, and ask our educators to tell us what we want to do in this new building.

254
00:31:09,675 --> 00:31:18,280
Based on all the nation, the architects will be presenting initial concepts this month to our building committee, which will be held, I believe, on January 14th.

255
00:31:18,320 --> 00:31:19,061
It's a Wednesday.

256
00:31:20,842 --> 00:31:23,183
What I've been told is that those will be like

257
00:31:24,794 --> 00:31:28,275
circles and shapes of where things might be on the property.

258
00:31:28,375 --> 00:31:33,016
So I think they want us to understand that this is a very beginning step.

259
00:31:34,396 --> 00:31:36,617
But we'll have initial cost estimates in February.

260
00:31:36,877 --> 00:31:41,078
And by June, we will have a design that will move forward.

261
00:31:41,518 --> 00:31:46,379
So although the paperwork seems to have taken an eternity, we're ready to move really quickly.

262
00:31:47,905 --> 00:31:54,767
I put out my own newsletter a couple of days ago that outlined some of these important steps in some more detail over the course of the next three months in particular.

263
00:31:55,727 --> 00:32:04,509
Please do tune into those opportunities to participate and provide input because this is a transformative that should have something for literally everyone in this city.

264
00:32:04,929 --> 00:32:12,431
This includes enhancing education for our students, making our vocational student services more available to the community and our seniors at large.

265
00:32:13,591 --> 00:32:21,535
preserving the pool, increasing the amount of field space that's available to our community sports teams, and creating a theater space that properly houses the arts we're so proud of.

266
00:32:23,616 --> 00:32:27,278
To my fellow elected officials being inducted today, welcome to the project.

267
00:32:27,758 --> 00:32:29,499
There is nowhere to hide.

268
00:32:32,761 --> 00:32:34,682
And this project is going to take all of us.

269
00:32:35,222 --> 00:32:36,263
I'm asking for your help.

270
00:32:37,459 --> 00:32:45,342
to make sure that we hear from all corners of our community and that we work together, despite how we may disagree, to bring this project to fruition.

271
00:32:45,922 --> 00:32:53,024
We need to work together to maximize our state reimbursement for the project and to create revenue streams that alleviate the project's cost for our residents.

272
00:32:53,785 --> 00:32:58,266
A state grant to pay for half of the total cost is a good start, but we can do more.

273
00:32:58,646 --> 00:32:59,807
This project is for Medford.

274
00:33:00,567 --> 00:33:02,088
and the road ahead will depend on all of us.

275
00:33:02,688 --> 00:33:04,869
Since this is my fourth inauguration, I'll be direct.

276
00:33:05,429 --> 00:33:12,633
In the spring of 2027, we will need to work together to pass a debt exclusion to pay for our share of the high school project possible.

277
00:33:13,193 --> 00:33:13,813
That will be us.

278
00:33:14,774 --> 00:33:18,255
I'll be calling on each of you to participate at every step and make sure that we get this done.

279
00:33:19,356 --> 00:33:27,920
I'm also super excited to announce that we've secured three MSBA grants to replace our roof and HVAC systems at the Roberts, the Missittuck, and the Brooks.

280
00:33:30,099 --> 00:33:32,562
Just like the McGlynn and the Andrews, these systems are old.

281
00:33:33,182 --> 00:33:35,785
They're at the end of their life and they require replacement.

282
00:33:36,286 --> 00:33:39,069
These grants will pay for more than half of each project.

283
00:33:39,910 --> 00:33:43,114
So in a few short years, we'll have modernized systems and a new high school.

284
00:33:52,043 --> 00:33:59,706
And maybe we can finally stop talking about the internet at Medford High, which I know would be a welcome change to the educators and the students who spend a lot of time there.

285
00:34:01,947 --> 00:34:09,790
So all those listening here in person, online, or later, if you'd like to watch public access television, please reach out any time.

286
00:34:10,511 --> 00:34:13,392
I take my role as an elected officiator seriously, and I care what's on your mind.

287
00:34:13,872 --> 00:34:16,533
Let's do this together, because for sure.

288
00:34:17,954 --> 00:34:18,214
Sorry.

289
00:34:19,694 --> 00:34:20,575
That's the best way forward.

290
00:34:20,875 --> 00:34:21,095
Thanks.

291
00:34:37,133 --> 00:34:42,655
So I just wanted to say, you know how they say that when you get married, if it rains, that's supposed to be good luck?

292
00:34:43,315 --> 00:34:47,757
Well, if you have an inauguration two times in a row and it snows, what does that mean?

293
00:34:49,077 --> 00:34:51,778
Something's telling me we made the right choice, so fantastic.

294
00:34:54,459 --> 00:35:02,562
At this time, I'd like to welcome up Bailey Kern to deliver the oath of office to Honorable Mayor Brianna Lunga.

295
00:35:11,110 --> 00:35:11,931
I was going to say, you see that?

296
00:35:21,178 --> 00:35:21,699
Class.

297
00:35:29,445 --> 00:35:30,466
I, state your name.

298
00:35:30,866 --> 00:35:32,027
I, Brianna Lungo Kern.

299
00:35:32,413 --> 00:35:39,415
do solemnly affirm that I will faithfully and impartially discharge and perform all the duties incumbent upon me as Mayor of the City of Medford.

300
00:35:48,418 --> 00:36:00,089
according to the best of my ability, and understanding, agreeable to the rules and regulations of the Constitution, the laws of this Commonwealth, and the ordinances of the City of Medford.

301
00:36:23,183 --> 00:36:24,184
Thank you, great job, great job.

302
00:36:26,727 --> 00:36:34,515
Congresswoman Clark, our state delegation, city council, school committee, my mother and father.

303
00:36:36,437 --> 00:36:41,422
Good morning and thank you for coming to the 2026 Medford inauguration.

304
00:36:43,180 --> 00:36:45,501
will be my state of the city too, so bear with me.

305
00:36:45,802 --> 00:36:48,523
I do want to get a lot in, and it's not everything.

306
00:36:48,563 --> 00:36:53,527
But I hope you've enjoyed our program so far this morning as much as I have.

307
00:36:53,927 --> 00:36:58,410
Thank you to Chris Sumer, our recovery coach, for bringing such energy to the hosting duties.

308
00:36:59,110 --> 00:37:03,873
Thank you to our newest poet laureate, Max Heinig, for his inspiring words, and Rabbi Jessica.

309
00:37:05,854 --> 00:37:13,417
Congresswoman Clark for sharing your perspectives and all that you do for us and the state, and everyone who's making this ceremony possible.

310
00:37:14,597 --> 00:37:27,461
Thank you to the team who planned this event, led by our Community Relations Director, Lisa Coliani, and Director of Communications, Steve Smerdy, and my Chief of Staff, who both are here, who helped me write this speech.

311
00:37:29,005 --> 00:37:40,159
I also want to take this opportunity to recognize the tireless work of our department heads, city staff, and volunteers who have continued to do so many amazing things despite the challenges that emerge from running a city.

312
00:37:42,853 --> 00:37:47,354
The people who work here are some of the brightest and most dedicated people I've had the pleasure of working with.

313
00:37:48,074 --> 00:37:53,515
So to everyone who works in this building and for the city as a whole, thank you for making Medford such a special place.

314
00:37:53,915 --> 00:37:59,396
What makes Medford so special can also make it challenging at times for us electeds and us managers.

315
00:38:00,676 --> 00:38:07,378
We're all passionate about our community, making it more sustainable, making it more affordable and making it more resilient for our future.

316
00:38:08,538 --> 00:38:09,418
But we are not perfect.

317
00:38:10,616 --> 00:38:12,698
Public service is not for the thin.

318
00:38:13,979 --> 00:38:16,021
It's hard and it's grueling and it takes a toll.

319
00:38:16,902 --> 00:38:24,969
But doing the hard work and making the hard decisions that you hope are the best decisions, and it's something we never take for granted.

320
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:29,733
There is a privilege in doing something hard and taking the criticism.

321
00:38:30,814 --> 00:38:36,119
There's a privilege in adjusting your look, listening to other voices and pivoting your view based on new information.

322
00:38:37,390 --> 00:38:40,671
There is a privilege in being tasked with guiding a community.

323
00:38:42,431 --> 00:38:46,332
For those getting inaugurated for another term, I know you share this with me.

324
00:38:46,952 --> 00:38:52,454
You wouldn't go the process of governing and campaigning again without having a deep desire.

325
00:38:52,854 --> 00:38:59,595
To those of you here for the first time, please cherish this moment and realize what is being bestowed upon you as an elected leader.

326
00:38:59,615 --> 00:39:01,576
Congratulations.

327
00:39:02,864 --> 00:39:14,574
Enjoy this day, cherish the road that brought you to this point, and never lose sight of the ultimate goal, serving all of the people of Medford with pride, purpose, and professionalism.

328
00:39:16,075 --> 00:39:21,400
I'm excited to continue the relationships with those reelected and forge new partnerships with those for the first time.

329
00:39:22,401 --> 00:39:29,207
We have a lot of hard work to do, but I have faith in this group, and I look forward to moving Medford forward together with you all.

330
00:39:31,393 --> 00:39:36,311
For more than four decades, Medford has been governed by a city charter that no longer reflected who we are.

331
00:39:37,401 --> 00:39:40,483
how we operate as a modern growing community.

332
00:39:40,983 --> 00:39:48,267
Written 40 years ago, our charter had become increasingly out of step with the needs of residents, city staff, and elected officials alike.

333
00:39:49,188 --> 00:40:00,955
As early as 2016, when I took my first vote as a city councilor to review the charter, I believe strongly that Medford deserved a governing document that was transparent, representative, and built for the future.

334
00:40:01,971 --> 00:40:19,515
Finally, together, our residents, our city council, our school committee, our state delegation, the Collins Center, myself, and most importantly, the Charter Task Force, advanced a charter that modernizes Medford's governance while respecting our values and traditions.

335
00:40:20,515 --> 00:40:28,157
This included changes to council representation, mayoral term limits and lengths, and the overall structure of city government.

336
00:40:29,103 --> 00:40:36,666
Thank you so much to the voters for recognizing the need to revamp the charter and sharing in our vision for a document that better serves our community.

337
00:40:39,067 --> 00:40:47,531
As we reflect on the progress we've made together, few conversations about the future of our city are as important as the work underway to update Medford zoning.

338
00:40:48,572 --> 00:40:56,235
Zoning shapes not just what we build, but how we live, how our corridors grow and how our community adapts to opportunities and challenges.

339
00:40:57,675 --> 00:41:02,296
This comprehensive review is essential to guiding Medford into the next decade and beyond.

340
00:41:03,756 --> 00:41:06,677
That said, the journey has not been without its challenges.

341
00:41:07,257 --> 00:41:14,978
The speed and scope were outpacing the capacity of our residents and staff, and we needed to refocus our efforts on better communication and public trust.

342
00:41:16,119 --> 00:41:22,680
Thank you to the Medford City Council for collaborating with me on a path forward that puts our community first in this process.

343
00:41:24,102 --> 00:41:38,915
We are extending our contract with the Innis Land Group to continue work through May 2026 on critical areas, including Medford Square, Tufts Institution, and Boston Avenue, while clearing the way for a broader request for proposals to be put out in March of 2026.

344
00:41:41,697 --> 00:41:46,822
As with all the work we do, we remain committed to open and transparent communication with the public.

345
00:41:47,662 --> 00:41:54,667
We know our responsibility on all issues, including rezoning, is to lead with honesty, accountability, and accountability no matter what.

346
00:41:57,169 --> 00:42:01,592
After years of careful planning, we have taken a major step towards revitalizing Medford Square.

347
00:42:02,533 --> 00:42:12,440
The city has selected Transcom Rail Estate as our partner in transforming three underutilized city-owned parcels behind City Hall into a vibrant mixed-use destination.

348
00:42:13,512 --> 00:42:20,957
This project will create a true village square atmosphere and ensure ample parking for our seniors and patrons of the Chevalier Theater.

349
00:42:22,178 --> 00:42:25,079
Transom's proposal reflects the values we share as a city.

350
00:42:25,700 --> 00:42:37,508
It includes both market rate and affordable housing anchored by 13,500 square foot grocery store across from our senior center and designed with pedestrian access and safety at the center.

351
00:42:38,388 --> 00:42:42,611
It is a vision that aligns with the comprehensive plan and advances the goals laid out in our RFP.

352
00:42:43,595 --> 00:42:47,236
Medford Square that is walkable, welcoming, and filled with opportunity.

353
00:42:49,556 --> 00:42:53,537
As we activate the square, we are reconnecting our city to one of the greatest natural assets.

354
00:42:53,757 --> 00:43:03,658
This past summer, the Clippership Connector opened, linking more than 10 miles of continuous waterfront greenways and inviting residents and visitors of Medford in a new way.

355
00:43:04,919 --> 00:43:07,199
We are already seeing the results of this renewed energy.

356
00:43:07,779 --> 00:43:12,860
The opening of the Great American Beer Hall has created a new regional strengthening in our commercial tax base,

357
00:43:13,573 --> 00:43:15,093
and brought new life to Mystic Avenue.

358
00:43:15,834 --> 00:43:20,215
We finally have a coffee shop in Medford Square and another new one in West Medford.

359
00:43:20,575 --> 00:43:27,057
Yet as we grow, we remain aware of the challenges those successes can bring, namely as it relates to affordable housing.

360
00:43:28,557 --> 00:43:32,278
Medford is confronting a housing crisis that is shared across the region and the nation.

361
00:43:33,379 --> 00:43:37,640
We are meeting it head on with a comprehensive approach that includes new funding tools,

362
00:43:38,338 --> 00:43:43,520
zoning reform, work from our affordable housing trust, and stronger development partnerships.

363
00:43:44,660 --> 00:43:58,265
Through firm negotiations, we secured tangible community benefits from our two 40B projects, safer streets, better transit access, more open space, and more affordable homes prioritized for Medford residents.

364
00:43:59,605 --> 00:44:03,767
I'm thrilled to see that both of these projects have shovels in the ground and are on their way to being built.

365
00:44:04,738 --> 00:44:09,986
Those two projects alone will bring in 161 affordable units to Medford.

366
00:44:10,747 --> 00:44:12,670
And we are ensuring that no one is left behind.

367
00:44:13,111 --> 00:44:15,054
Our commitment to veterans is unwavering.

368
00:44:16,056 --> 00:44:18,139
To many veterans facing housing instability,

369
00:44:18,822 --> 00:44:29,210
Through a meaningful partnership with our office, our city, the Veterans Service Office, American Post Legion 45, Suffolk Construction, we are taking a critical step.

370
00:44:29,450 --> 00:44:41,959
Together we are working to transform the American Legion site at 321 Winthrop Street into transitional housing that will provide veterans with stability and a clear path forward towards permanent housing.

371
00:44:43,088 --> 00:44:45,249
This effort reflects the best of Medford.

372
00:44:45,910 --> 00:44:54,034
Suffolk Construction has stepped up to fund a full feasibility study for the project and committed an additional $15,000 in facility upgrades.

373
00:44:55,034 --> 00:45:01,018
Through a community fund grant, the city is investing alongside them to ensure this project moves forward with care and intention.

374
00:45:01,698 --> 00:45:07,141
That is what true public-private partnership looks like, shared responsibility, shared purpose, and shared impact.

375
00:45:09,325 --> 00:45:11,887
As our city grows, so does activity in our neighborhoods.

376
00:45:12,667 --> 00:45:19,412
New residential and commercial projects bring new energy, new foot traffic, and inevitably more vehicles on our streets.

377
00:45:20,213 --> 00:45:25,997
Growing demands that we plan not just for today, but for how people move safely and efficiently through Medford tomorrow.

378
00:45:26,797 --> 00:45:32,021
That is why we are making deliberate investments to improve traffic flow and create safer streets across our community.

379
00:45:32,853 --> 00:45:43,516
Through our complete streets initiatives in places like Haines Square and Riverside Avenue, we are redesigning roadways to better serve every driver, cyclist, pedestrians, and transit users alike.

380
00:45:44,796 --> 00:45:53,299
In collaboration with MassDOT, our state delegation, and the city council, we've advanced plans to reconstruct high crash intersections along Main Street.

381
00:45:54,639 --> 00:45:57,420
I want to thank our traffic and transportation team for leading this work.

382
00:45:58,141 --> 00:46:00,143
and for expanding blue bikes across the city.

383
00:46:00,984 --> 00:46:09,073
We now have 16 stations making sustainable transportation more accessible than ever, with the hope of opening three more in 2026.

384
00:46:10,775 --> 00:46:13,958
Safe, well-designed streets are not just a transportation priority.

385
00:46:14,499 --> 00:46:17,442
They are central to our development goals and to the safety of our neighborhoods.

386
00:46:18,168 --> 00:46:22,351
To support that vision, we are investing in the basics, our roads and sidewalks.

387
00:46:23,192 --> 00:46:31,118
With the dedication of our engineering team and Department of Public Works, we are making steady progress, although slow, on the decades of backlog.

388
00:46:32,319 --> 00:46:39,984
This year, we invested hundreds of thousands in sidewalks repairs and completed patchwork improvements on seven of our more heavily traveled roads.

389
00:46:40,665 --> 00:46:47,390
We have significant sidewalk repair on Salem Street, Park Street, and at the intersection of Spring and Central Avenue, just to name a few.

390
00:46:48,372 --> 00:46:58,197
We are also investing in our urban canopy and neighborhood appearance, removing nearly 400 tree stumps in 2025 and planting 200 new trees once again.

391
00:46:59,257 --> 00:47:03,219
Thanks to this amazing work, we now have less than 100 stumps left on our current list.

392
00:47:03,919 --> 00:47:05,520
We have not seen a number this low since 2009.

393
00:47:05,600 --> 00:47:15,045
We have also made targeted investments in the facilities at both Andrews and McGlynn to ensure our buildings support safe and conducive learning environments.

394
00:47:16,198 --> 00:47:26,927
We are beginning the work thanks to a second MSBA grant on the roofs at Missitech, Roberts, and Brooks, another $20 to $25 million undertaking that the state will help fund.

395
00:47:27,688 --> 00:47:33,653
These investments are essential to maintaining strong, reliable school buildings, value we place on education in Medford.

